c:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both RankMath and Serpstat share a solid foundation of core features including Keyword Research, Rank Tracking, Content Optimization, Serp Analysis. Where RankMath pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Ai Writing, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on this capability. On the other hand, Serpstat uniquely offers Site Audit and Backlink Analysis and Competitor Analysis and Api Access, giving it an edge for users who prioritize these areas. \n\nLooking at user ratings, RankMath holds an overall score of 8/10 and an ease of use score of 8/10, while Serpstat scores 7/10 overall and 6/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
d:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, RankMath offers a more budget-friendly entry point at Free, compared to Serpstat's starting price of $69/mo. RankMath has a notable advantage here with its free plan, allowing you to get started without any financial commitment. Serpstat does not currently offer a free tier, which means you will need to pay from day one."}]]}]
