10:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. RankMath is best suited for WordPress users, bloggers, small business sites, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Serpstat, meanwhile, shines for SMBs, in house SEOs, budget teams, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2018, RankMath describes itself as \"Advanced WordPress SEO plugin with AI-powered content optimization.\" Serpstat, established in 2013, positions itself as \"Growth hacking SEO tool for keyword research, rank tracking, and site audit.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
11:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **RankMath** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 7.0), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Serpstat is a poor choice — far from it. Serpstat excels in its own right, particularly for SMBs and in house SEOs.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value generous free version with advanced features, go with RankMath. If good value for comprehensive features matters more to you, Serpstat is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
